## 7. Process Notes / What The Gates Caught This Session

The CAD gates earned their keep again — staff-engineer's MANUAL pressure-testing (not the green suite) caught every real defect:
- **M2 tightening:** SE caught over-broadening on untested inputs (`convert the database schema`) across 3 cycles; forced the principled CATEGORY RULE instead of example-fitting.
- **FU-6:** SE BLOCKED on C3 (`what is the architecture`→mechanical) and surfaced FU-8 (`how to run the tests`→UNKNOWN) — both invisible to a 100%-green suite. This is the core lesson, AGAIN: a green misuse-first suite proves the tested cases, NOT the untested adjacent inputs. SE pressure-testing beyond the qa corpus is load-bearing.
- **Sage drift to watch:** I twice drafted user-questions anticipating a BLOCK that came back PASS, and once put a stale SHA (7af2c9e) in a tag directive — deployment-engineer correctly HALTED on the mismatch. Halt-and-verify discipline caught the Sage error. Lesson: verify HEAD/SHA from git BEFORE writing it into a directive; don't guess.
- **Parallel-batch hazard:** compound bash with `echo`/`||` or one exit-1 grep cancels the WHOLE parallel tool batch (including dispatches). Keep release-critical dispatches in their own message, not batched with probe commands.

